Enum Class GBuilder

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<GBuilder>
org.interworldtransport.cladosG.GBuilder
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<GBuilder>, Constable
public enum GBuilder extends Enum<GBuilder>
This builder gets basic information and constructs many Clados Geometry objects.

This enumeration has NO non-static element for the instance, thus GBuilder HAS NO INTERNAL STATE that can change.

Version:
2.0
Author:
Dr Alfred W Differ

    • copyOfScale

      public static final <T extends ProtoN & Field & Normalizable> Scale<T> copyOfScale(Scale<T> pIn)
      Simple copy method. Offer a Scale, get a copy of it back as far as mapped values go.
      Type Parameters:
      T - generic description of a CladosF number. Descends from ProtoN but must also implement Field and Normalizable.
      Parameters:
      pIn - The Scale object to be imitated.
      Returns:
      new Scale object that RE-USES blades from the contained basis, but copies all numbers ensuring the two Scale objects do NOT share values in their internal maps.

    • createFootLike

      public static final Foot createFootLike(String pName)
      This method creates a new Foot object with one Cardinal re-used from the Foot to be imitated but the Foot has a new name too.
      This method would EASILY cause a runtime error with an index out of bounds complaint if the suggested spot for the Cardinal is out of range. Instead of that runtime error, it detects for this and returns null for the cardinal instead. That isn't and issue for the Foot constructor because 'null' will be added to the cardinal list. 'null' IS A VALID CARDINAL conceptually speaking.
      Parameters:
      pName - New string name for Foot to be created.
      Returns:
      Foot (new instance)

    • createGProduct

      public static final GProduct createGProduct(Optional<Basis> pB, String pSig) throws BadSignatureException
      This method constructs a GProduct using the offered basis and signature. It first checks the product cache and returns a matching product instead of constructing a new one IF it is found. If not, it deposits the offered Basis in the cache and then calls the method for creating a product that does not try to re-use a basis. The net result works the same, though, since that other method checks the basis cache before making a new basis. By the end of the method, both basis and product caches are populated with anything that had to be constructed.
      Parameters:
      pB - Basis to re-use in constructing product
      pSig - String form of the product's signature
      Returns:
      GProduct constructed
      Throws:
      BadSignatureException - Thrown if the pSig parameter is malformed

    • createGProduct

      public static final GProduct createGProduct(String pSig) throws BadSignatureException
      This method constructs a GProduct using the offered signature String. It first checks the product cache and returns a matching product instead of constructing a new one IF it is found. If not, it checks the basis cache for a match to decide which product constructor to use. By the end of the method, both basis and product caches are populated with anything that had to be constructed.
      Parameters:
      pSig - String form of the product's signature
      Returns:
      GProduct constructed
      Throws:
      BadSignatureException - Thrown if the pSig parameter is malformed

    • createScale

      public static final <T extends ProtoN & Field & Normalizable> Scale<T> createScale(CladosField pMode, Basis pB, Cardinal pCard)
      Scale constructor #2 covered with this method. This is the "No map of blade to T available" constructor that dishes up a complete Scale of T with zeroes for weights.
      Type Parameters:

      Parameters:
      pMode - CladosField enumeration so we know what kind of ProtoN to expect from get()
      pB - Basis to which the blades used in the internal map belong.
      pCard - Incoming Cardinal to reference here.
      Returns:
      Scale of T requested using the offered mode, basis, and cardinal.

    • pscalarOfMonad

      public static final <T extends ProtoN & Field & Normalizable> Monad pscalarOfMonad(Monad pM)
      This method builds a copy of the offered monad with a slightly different name and then completely swaps out the weights to ensure it is a pscalar that otherwise passes all reference tests.
      Type Parameters:
      T - ProtoN child number to create. Includes the Field and Normalizable interfaces too.
      Parameters:
      pM - Monad to be mostly copied in constructing a pscalar for it.
      Returns:
      Monad that is a unit pscalar that otherwise matches the offered Monad.

    • validateBasisSize

      public static final boolean validateBasisSize(byte pGen)

      This method just calls the method of the same name in the CanonicalBasis interface. It is here for convenience.
      Parameters:
      pGen - byte integer of number of generators for the test
      Returns:
      TRUE if integer is in the supported range. FALSE otherwise.

    • validateSignature

      public static final boolean validateSignature(String pSig)
      Tests the signature string to see if it contains the correct chars and no more of them than can be supported.
      This method just calls the method of the same name in the CliffordProduct interface. It is here for convenience.
      Parameters:
      pSig - String signature to be tested
      Returns:
      TRUE if string is composed of '+' and '-' chars, but not too many. FALSE otherwise.
